main event: On 6 October 1959, two civilians in Northern Wisconsin observed a brightly glowing, cigar-shaped object emitting bluish-white light moving at a high rate of speed before disappearing from sight.
interesting points: The object was described as cigar-shaped with a bluish-white light.,Observers heard four distinct sounds, similar to an atom bomb, after the object disappeared.,Objects were seen moving in an arc at high speed for approximately 20 minutes.,A total of 3 adults witnessed the object.,No evidence was found that definitively identified the object.
witness description: two civilians, both affiliated with the Wisconsin Conservation Department
